Armando ALFONSO, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7538. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit Dec. 21, 1934. In forma pauperis. Aquilino Lopez, Jr., of Key West, Fla., for appellant. John W. Holland, U. S. Atty., of Jacksonville, Fla., and W. Sanders Gramling, Asst. U. S. Atty.,- of Miami, Fla.

Before BRYAN, FOSTER, and WALKER, Circuit. Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
